name: Quiet Evening at Historic Long Wharf Harbor
description:
This image, "Quiet Evening at Historic Long Wharf Harbor" depicts a photograph taken as the sun was setting at the historic Long Wharf Harbor. The harbor located in Cambridge, Maryland USA was once a waterfront site where slaves were sold; and shipped to plantations in the Deep South. In the 18th century, the town of Cambridge was one of several centers for the slave trade. Here, kidnapped Africans were brought and sold until the trans-Atlantic slave trade was outlawed. Today, historical markers reveal its history.

  The image was created with the assistance of artificial intelligence (AI). The process for creating this image included using a photograph, algorithms, and artificial intelligence.
